Heyam AbdalrahmanHeyam Abdalrahman • 3.+ • 3.+ (HR) Public Relations and Marketing | Administrative Manager & Talent Acquisition | Training & Development(HR) Public Relations and Marketing | Administrative Manager & Talent Acquisition | Training & Development
2 d • 2 dni temu
HR:
I rejected a CV from a candidate twice.

He applied for the third time, and I called him for an interview.

And guess what? We offered him a role right after the interview.

Now, a year later, he has become the Team Leader and is performing excellently.

The lesson I learned from this: do not always judge a person solely based on their CV.

Sometimes, they are more than that one-page profile.

Give a chance to candidates; they have energy and ideas more than you can think of.

#منقول
Czy to dobra rekomendacja?

Nr publikacji w kanale 6

Sugerowane
Vin VashishtaVin Vashishta • 3.+ • 3.+ AI Advisor | Author “From Data To Profit” | Course Instructor (Data & AI Strategy, Product Management, Leadership)AI Advisor | Author “From Data To Profit” | Course Instructor (Data & AI Strategy, Product Management, Leadership)
2 d • 2 dni temu
We need to abandon the notion that removing bias and toxic content from massive datasets is feasible. It doesn’t work yet and there are dozens of examples to support that.

When Google and Reddit signed their $60 million data-sharing agreement, I said there was no way to remove all the toxicity in the dataset, and it would inevitably leak through.

Redditors are masters of being subtly inappropriate to avoid suspension and skirting content moderation rules. This dataset is the worst-case scenario for cleaning.

Multiple people, most working in data science roles, insisted that Google could do it. They said the approaches were well-known and effective.

And now we’re watching Gemini leak comically inappropriate answers that have been traced back to Reddit posts and comments.

Removing bias and objectionable content at scale is a huge challenge. We don’t have a comprehensive way to automate it. Using people to find and filter datasets creates entirely new problems.

Businesses can’t push LLMs into customers’ hands if they don’t understand the data used to train them. A small, high-quality data source does more for LLMs than a massive mid-quality one.

Small models with targeted applications are proving increasingly successful. I’m not sure how many more Tays and Geminis we need to see before people change their ways…

But it doesn’t seem like we’re done making this mistake.

#GenAI #Gemini #DataQuality

Meet Googler Avtansh Pandey, a software engineer working on Google’s Node OS Dev team, who moved to Poland to make his dream of working at Google come true.

“I wanted to be able to contribute to the impact Google has, and hence started looking for opportunities and found one in Poland aligned to my interests,” says Avtansh. “They helped me with a range of services and also acknowledged the range of differences one might face from local language to accommodation.”

In addition to his role as a software engineer, Avtansh is on the Noogler Onboarding team, where he helps new Googlers get accustomed to the company’s culture. He also represented Google at a recent charity basketball tournament in Krakow.

A great example of how to use voice mode for interview prep. How are others using ChatGPT to rehearse or prepare?
John SeatonJohn Seaton • 3.+ • 3.+ Enabling transformative outcomes through collaboration solutions. "I make complex simple". Video creator, YouTuber and Podcaster.Enabling transformative outcomes through collaboration solutions. "I make complex simple". Video creator, YouTuber and Podcaster.
1 t • 1 tydzień temu
Need someone to practice your interview skills with?

Have you tried ChatGPT?

After seeing the latest ChatGPT4o demos, I thought....can it help candidates with their interviewing skills?

In this example, I play the role of a High School graduate who has obtained a cyber security certificate from Cisco Networking Academy. I know I look old - but work with me here 😉

Pay attention to my prompts and the feedback that ChatGPT provides. It is truly amazing.

Let me know your 🤔 thoughts on this.

FYI - This used ChatGPT 3.5 - not ChatGPT4o - so it should improve even more.

#interviewingskills #chatGPT
